<subSubSection id="C33817ADFFFB8437E68AFB1F6CFDFA3E" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFFB8437E68AFB1F6CFDFA3E" blockId="1.[151,1436,1352,1523]" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFFB8437E68AFB1F6E4FFAAF" bold="true" box="[151,274,1352,1378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C223FA5FFFB8437E701FB1F6EC9FAAF" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1902" box="[284,404,1352,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Glabellula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFFB8437E701FB1F6EC9FAAF" box="[284,404,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">Glabellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of minute flies, 
<quantity id="4CDAE9C3FFFB8437E4A0FB1E6C42FAAE" box="[701,799,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1−2 mm</quantity>
in length; usually shiny black, with or without yellow markings; pubescence sparse, minute. The genus is distinguished from all other mythicomyiids based on the medial interruption of sclerotization on abdominal tergite 2 and in the wing by the tiny marginal cell of the wing formed by vein 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFFB8437E6D3FBE26FA7FA18" box="[206,250,1461,1493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">
R 
<subScript id="17A64663FFFB8437E6C2FB906FA7FA18" attach="left" box="[223,250,1479,1493]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">2+3</subScript>
</emphasis>
joining 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFFB8437E74BFBE26E32FA18" box="[342,367,1461,1493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">
R 
<subScript id="17A64663FFFB8437E77AFB906E32FA18" attach="left" box="[359,367,1479,1493]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
well before the costa, combined with cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFFB8437E559FBE36C3BFA03" box="[836,870,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">bm</emphasis>
united with cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFFB8437E202FBE36B1CFA03" box="[1055,1089,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">dm</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFFB8437E252FBE36BCFFA02" box="[1103,1170,1460,1487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="206">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) (reformulated after the versions presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB339D7FFFB8437E78CFB8F6DC2FA3E" author="Hall, J. C. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[401,671,1496,1523]" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" pagination="281 - 320" refId="ref6381" refString="Hall, J. C. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (1984) Family Bombyliidae. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region. Vol. V, Part 13, No. 4. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 281 - 320." type="book chapter" year="1984">Hall &amp; Evenhuis (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB339D7FFFB8437E4C8FB8F6CC1FA3E" author="Evenhuis, N. L." box="[725,924,1496,1523]" pageId="1" pageNumber="206" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref5986" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. (2019) The genus Glabellula Bezzi (Diptera: Mythicomyiidae) in Australia, with descriptions of new species. Bishop Museum Occasional Papers, 127, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="2019">Evenhuis (2019))</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
